title: Walker's European, Canadian trips cost nearly $147,000
text:
Walker's European, Canadian trips cost nearly $147,000 Records: Walker's European, Canadian trade missions cost state nearly $147,000 Published On: Oct 09 2015 05:45:03 PM CDT Updated On: Oct 09 2015 05:47:50 PM CDT Channel3000.com file photo MADISON, Wis. - 
Newly released records show two of Republican Gov. Scott Walker's international trips this year cost the state nearly $147,000. Related Content GOP plan would dismantle GAB, replace with partisan commission 
The Wisconsin Economic Development Corp. released records late Friday afternoon that show Walker's trade mission to Europe in April cost $117,300. His trade mission to Canada in June cost $29,470. 
According to the data, both trips came in under budget. The European trip was projected to cost $165,250 and the Canada trip $34,152. 
Expenses on both trips included hotels, transportation, parking, telecommunications, hospitality gifts, networking events and meals.
